( sgn ( x + y ) ) <= ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 )
proof
A1: (y = ( 0 ) implies ( sgn ( x + y ) ) <= ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ))
proof
assume A2: y = ( 0 );
then ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ) = ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( 0 ) ) + 1 ) by CKB15:def 1
.= ( ( sgn x ) + 1 );
hence thesis by A2,XREAL_1:29;
end;
A3: ((( 0 ) < x & ( 0 ) < y) implies ( sgn ( x + y ) ) <= ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ))
proof
( sgn x ) < ( ( sgn x ) + 1 ) by XREAL_1:29;
then A4: ( ( sgn x ) + ( 0 ) ) < ( ( ( sgn x ) + 1 ) + 1 ) by XREAL_1:8;
assume A5: (( 0 ) < x & ( 0 ) < y);
then (( sgn x ) = 1 & ( sgn y ) = 1) by CKB15:def 1;
hence thesis by A5,A4,CKB15:def 1;
end;
A6: ((x < ( 0 ) & ( 0 ) < y) implies ( sgn ( x + y ) ) <= ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ))
proof
assume that
A7: x < ( 0 )
and
A8: ( 0 ) < y;
( sgn x ) = ( - 1 ) by A7,CKB15:def 1;
then A9: ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ) = 1 by A8,CKB15:def 1;
((( x + y ) < ( 0 ) or ( x + y ) = ( 0 )) or ( 0 ) < ( x + y ));
hence thesis by A9,CKB15:def 1;
end;
A10: ((( 0 ) < x & y < ( 0 )) implies ( sgn ( x + y ) ) <= ( ( ( sgn x ) + ( sgn y ) ) + 1 ))
proof
